[2;36m                    [0m         +            [1;35mexif_log[0m[1m([0mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG,                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +                     [32m"ExifData"[0m,                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +                     [32m"Tag offset field exceeds buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u + 8 + 4 > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m,          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +                     offset, size[1m)[0m;                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +            return [1;36m0[0m;                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +        [1m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +        doff = [1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1m([0md + offset + [1;36m8[0m, data->priv->order[1m)[0m;                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +    [1m}[0m else [1m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +        doff = offset + [1;36m8[0m;                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +    [1m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +    [35m/[0m* Sanity check: entire data payload must lie within buffer *[35m/[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +    if [1m([0m[1m([0munsigned int[1m)[0mdoff >= size || [1m([0munsigned int[1m)[0ms > size - [1m([0munsigned int[1m)[0mdoff[1m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +        [1;35mexif_log[0m[1m([0mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG,                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +                 [32m"ExifData"[0m,                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +                 [32m"Tag data extends beyond buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u + %u > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m,                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +                 doff, s, size[1m)[0m;                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +        return [1;36m0[0m;                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +    [1m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +    [35m/[0m* Allocate and copy the tag payload *[35m/[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +    entry->data = [1;35mexif_data_alloc[0m[1m([0mdata, s[1m)[0m;                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +    if [1m([0m!entry->data[1m)[0m [1m{[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +        [1;35mEXIF_LOG_NO_MEMORY[0m[1m([0mdata->priv->log, [32m"ExifData"[0m, s[1m)[0m;                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +        return [1;36m0[0m;                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +    [1m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +    entry->size = s;                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +    [1;35mmemcpy[0m[1m([0mentry->data, d + doff, s[1m)[0m;                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                        [32m"MakerNote found [0m[32m([0m[32m%02x %02x %02x [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m%02x "[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                        [32m"%02x %02x %02x...[0m[32m)[0m[32m."[0m,               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                        entry->data[1m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1m][0m, entry->data[1m[[0m[1;36m1[0m[1m][0m,      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA heap-buffer-overflow was detected in libexif’s data-loading logic when running [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe `exif_from_data_fuzzer`. AddressSanitizer reports an out-of-bounds [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-byte read[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the function `exif_data_load_data_entry` while copying data from a heap buffer [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat is only [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes long. The crash is triggered during the fuzzer’s call to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_new_from_data` on malformed input.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue Overview  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  During fuzz testing with `exif_from_data_fuzzer`, AddressSanitizer flags a [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmulti-byte heap-buffer-overflow in libexif. The error arises in the call to [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`__asan_memcpy` within `exif_data_load_data_entry` when copying [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes just past [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe end of an allocated [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte region.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability Type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  This is a heap-buffer-overflow vulnerability [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmulti-byte read past allocated [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Key Observations  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The crash stack trace shows the overflow originates at  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif-data.[0m[1;92mc:213[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, propagates through  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    `exif_data_load_data_content` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif-data.[0m[1;92mc:531[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    `exif_data_load_data` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif-data.[0m[1;92mc:984[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and is ultimately reached via  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    `exif_data_new_from_data` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif-data.[0m[1;92mc:159[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which is invoked by the fuzzer [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mharness.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The buffer in question is allocated via `operator new` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmalloc under the hood[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith a size of [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes, but a memcpy of size [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m is performed starting at offset [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m207[0m[39m, leading to an out-of-bounds read.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • AddressSanitizer’s shadow-byte output confirms that the read occurs immediately[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mafter the valid heap region’s end.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code Areas for Investigation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  To gain a full understanding of the root cause, the following parts of the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodebase should be reviewed:  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Function `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m in exif-data.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m — logic [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdetermining entry size and memcpy parameters.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Function `exif_data_load_data_content` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m531[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m — handling of [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconcatenated data entries.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Function `exif_data_load_data` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m984[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m — orchestration of content [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloading loops.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Function `exif_data_new_from_data` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m159[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m — entry point for parsing [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mraw EXIF data.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Data structures governing EXIF entry offsets, lengths, and buffer allocations.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo assumptions are made about underlying causes beyond the observable overflow. The[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpf9lyg626[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is a heap-buffer-overflow detected by AddressSanitizer when [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrunning `exif_from_data_fuzzer` against `libexif`’s `exif_data_load_data_entry`. [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer log shows a [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-byte read immediately past a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte heap allocation, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtriggered by `memcpy` in `exif_data_load_data_entry`.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA patch was attempted in `libexif/exif-data.c` to add explicit bounds checks around[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe offset field and data payload, consolidate sanity checks, and then copy only [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen the entire payload lies within the buffer. After applying the patch, [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompilation fails with multiple errors: extraneous parentheses, misuse of the comma[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moperator in format strings, unmatched braces, and an unrecognized `data` [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentifier.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A libFuzzer run on `exif_from_data_fuzzer` reports:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • ASan reports a multi-byte heap-buffer-overflow at `__asan_memcpy` in [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry`.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • The overflow is a [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-byte read starting exactly one byte past a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocated region.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Stack trace flows from `exif_data_load_data_entry` → [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_content` → `exif_data_load_data` → `exif_data_new_from_data` →[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • The allocation comes from `malloc` in the fuzzer driver.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Shadow memory indicates the read touches the first byte of the redzone [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmediately after the allocated block.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Observations  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The code distinguishes inline data [0m[1;39m([0m[39m≤[0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m versus out-of-line data [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfield[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - There are existing checks for `doff >= size` and `s > size - doff`, but the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcrash shows they are insufficient or bypassed for certain malformed inputs.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow happens in `[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` when `d + doff` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlies at the very end of the buffer.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch restructures the code to:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • First verify that the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte offset field [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is inside the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer before reading it.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Compute `doff` only if that check passes.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Unify the sanity checks to ensure `doff + s` does not exceed `size`.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Allocate `entry->data` and then call `memcpy` only after both checks.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch also cleans up the “MakerNote” handling that follows the `memcpy`.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Compilation Errors After Patch  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Error: “extraneous ‘[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m’ before ‘;’” at the `entry->data[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m6[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` call in a logging [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstatement [0m[1;39m([0m[39munbalanced parentheses or stray comma operator[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Warnings: misuse of the comma operator around format strings—expressions have [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mno effect.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Error: “unknown type name ‘data’” and subsequent errors around brace matching [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand unreachable `return` statements in the “MakerNote” section.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch’s diff context shows misaligned indentation and unmatched braces, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating the new code wasn’t properly merged with the existing `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->tag ==[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mEXIF_TAG_MAKER_NOTE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` block.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The implementation of `exif_data_load_data_entry` and surrounding functions [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`exif_data_load_data_content`, `exif_data_load_data`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to understand all code paths[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat compute `doff` and call `memcpy`.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The logging/formatting macros and how the “MakerNote found [0m[1;39m([0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m” messages are [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructed, since format-string misuse may hide logic errors.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The data structures in `ExifDataPriv` [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `offset_mnote`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and how they are [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mset or used after reading tag data.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any helper routines used for byte-order handling [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_get_long`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and buffer [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mslicing to see if additional preconditions are needed.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow was triggered in `libexif`’s [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry` when a malformed TIFF/EXIF entry caused `memcpy` to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mread past the end of an allocated buffer. The user’s patch attempt added explicit [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds checks around the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte offset field and unified the payload sanity checks [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore allocating and copying the data. However, running the same fuzzer input [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39magainst the patched code still reproduces a heap-buffer-overflow at the same site [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:223[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, indicating the added checks did not prevent the out-of-bounds [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mread.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer harness invokes `exif_data_new_from_data`, which in turn calls [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry`.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Inside `exif_data_load_data_entry`, the code calculates a data‐offset [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`doff`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand size [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`s`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, allocates an entry buffer of `s` bytes, then calls [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- For a specially crafted input, `doff + s` exceeds the length of the input buffer [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`size`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, so `memcpy` reads beyond the allocated region, triggering a [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow in AddressSanitizer.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImportant Observations from the Initial Log  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Crash at `__asan_memcpy` invoked from `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39moriginal line [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m213[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow happens [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes past a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte region at address `[0m[1;36m0x511000000180[0m[39m`, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtrying to read [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes at offset `[0m[1;36m0x24f[0m[39m`.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The region was allocated by `malloc` for `entry->data` with size `s` and is too [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msmall to hold the requested copy.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch refactors the branch deciding `doff`. If `s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`, it first checks that [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte offset field [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m lies within the buffer. If that passes, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mit reads `doff`. Otherwise it bails out.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In either branch, it then verifies `doff < size` and `s <= size - doff` before [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Finally it allocates `entry->data = [0m[1;35mexif_data_alloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` and calls [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` only if both checks pass.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mLog After Applying the Patch  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer run still aborts in AddressSanitizer due to a heap-buffer-overflow, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnow at the updated source line number `exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:223[0m[39m`.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The log shows the same allocations and boundaries as before, meaning the new [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msanity checks did not catch this malformed case.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Calculation of `doff` when `s <= [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m` vs. `s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`—verify integer casts and [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpotential wrap-around or sign issues.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. The correctness of the condition `[0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned int[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > size` for [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidating the offset field.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Consistency of type promotions for `offset`, `s`, and `size` [0m[1;39m([0m[39msigned vs. [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munsigned[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Interaction between TIFF directory parsing [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhere `offset` and `s` are first [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomputed[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and this copy logic.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Any places earlier in the parsing chain where malformed entries could lead to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvalid `offset` or `s` values slipping through.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Other similar code paths in `exif-data.c` [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., loading other data types, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnested directories[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for equivalent off-by-one or insufficient boundary checks.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. The behavior of `exif_data_alloc`—whether it can return a smaller buffer than [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrequested under out-of-memory conditions or alignment constraints.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpf9lyg626[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer harness triggered an AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow in libexif’s [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry`, where a `memcpy` reads beyond an allocated buffer. A [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch was introduced that adds several bounds checks—verifying declared payload [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize does not exceed the input buffer, ensuring the [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m-byte IFD entry header is [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minside the buffer, confirming the data pointer and payload lie within bounds, and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogging debug messages on any violation. After applying these checks and adjusting [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe `doff` computation, the same heap-buffer-overflow crash still occurs at the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msame location in `exif_data_load_data_entry`. [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Initial Issue**  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer run with AddressSanitizer reports a heap-buffer-overflow when [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessing a crafted EXIF buffer.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash stack trace points to `__asan_memcpy` in `exif_data_load_data_entry`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`libexif/exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:213:3[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow happens when reading [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes starting exactly at the end of a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m207[0m[39m-byte heap buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;36m0x511000000180[0m[39m … [0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, i.e., reading one byte [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpast the allocated region.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Downstream calls are in `exif_data_load_data_content`, `exif_data_load_data`, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand finally `exif_data_new_from_data`.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Important Observations in the Initial Issue**  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The buffer overflow is reproducible deterministically by the fuzzer.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The offending code invokes `[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, where `d` is [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe raw input data and `doff+s` exceeds the buffer.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No preliminary checks in the original code prevent this out-of-bounds read for[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcertain malformed or truncated EXIF entries.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Patch Attempt**  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Inserted a check that declared size `s` must not exceed `size` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe total [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minput buffer length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensured the IFD entry header [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m12[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m starting at `offset` is entirely [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithin `size`.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Split data offset computation into two cases:  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • If `s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`, read a [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte pointer at `d + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m`.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Otherwise, use the inline field at `offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m`.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added a check that `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff + s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m <= size` before allocation or copy.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Reorganized allocation and copy logic, emitting debug logs on errors and [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturning early.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Result After Patch**  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer run still aborts with the same AddressSanitizer report, pointing to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe same line in `exif_data_load_data_entry`.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The heap buffer is still [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes long and the overflow still reads [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat offset [0m[1;36m0x4f[0m[39m from the buffer start.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No change in crash location or ASan diagnostics: the new bounds checks did not[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevent the out-of-bounds read in this test case.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Areas for Further Investigation**  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The computation of `offset` and `doff` in relation to the overall IFD [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructure parsing logic.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The code in `exif_data_load_data_content` and `exif_data_load_data` that [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39miterates IFD entries and supplies the `offset`, `s`, and `size` parameters.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The handling of multi-entry IFD blocks and maker-note recursion, which may [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maffect how `offset` and `size` are scoped for nested data areas.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Potential integer signedness or overflow issues when computing `offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand `doff + s`.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any assumptions about the buffer layout made by `exif_get_long` or by upstream[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry count parsing, overall buffer length passed to [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_new_from_data`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo suspected root cause or fix is proposed here; the report focuses on the observed[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbehavior, the attempted mitigations, and the remaining failure point for deeper [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode review.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Container overflow:      fc[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Array cookie:            ac[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Intra object redzone:    bb[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ASan internal:           fe[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Left alloca redzone:     ca[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Right alloca redzone:    cb[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m==[0m[1;36m18[0m[39m==ABORTING[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubprocess command returned a non-zero exit status: [0m[1;36m1[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/qqor/aixcc/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mlibexif[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpf9lyg626[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe codebase was exhibiting a heap-buffer-overflow in libexif’s [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_data_load_data_entry function, triggered by a fuzz test [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`exif_from_data_fuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. An AddressSanitizer report showed a [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-byte read beyond [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man allocated [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte buffer when processing an IFD entry. To mitigate this, a [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch was attempted in `libexif/exif-data.c` that computes and checks each entry’s [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbase and size before calling `exif_data_load_data_entry`. After applying the patch,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe build failed catastrophically with dozens of “function definition is not [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallowed here” errors in `exif-data.c`, indicating unbalanced or misplaced braces.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A LibFuzzer run [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_from_data_fuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with AddressSanitizer enabled [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcrashed on a heap-buffer-overflow.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow occurred in `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m of exif-data.c[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen reading [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes at an offset equal to the buffer’s end.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Call stack highlights:  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `exif_data_load_data_entry` → `exif_data_load_data_content` → [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data` → `exif_data_new_from_data` → `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The corrupted address [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m lies just past a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte heap [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation, confirming out-of-bounds reading of entry data.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Location: In `libexif/exif-data.c`, inside the loop over directory entries [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m527[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Original code fragment [0m[1;39m([0m[39msimplified[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_entry[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, entry, d, ds,[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                   offset + [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m * i[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mexif_content_add_entry[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->ifd[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mifd[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, entry[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mexif_entry_unref[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Patched code adds a block with computed `entry_base` and `entry_size`:[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         unsigned int entry_base = offset + [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m * i;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         unsigned int entry_size = ds - entry_base;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry_size >= [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m &&[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_entry[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, entry,[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                       d + entry_base,[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                       entry_size, [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35mexif_content_add_entry[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->ifd[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mifd[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, entry[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mexif_entry_unref[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Goal: ensure each entry’s data pointer and length stay within the containing [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msegment.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Result and Build Errors  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Compilation produced ~[0m[1;36m20[0m[39m errors of the form:[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     exif-data.c:<line>:[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: error: function definition is not allowed here[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ^[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Errors span multiple unrelated lines [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m548[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m557[0m[39m, …, [0m[1;36m1247[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, indicating a brace [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimbalance or misplaced `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` that cascades through the file.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch likely disrupted the block structure in `exif-data.c`, causing the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompiler to interpret code as nested function definitions.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The loop and surrounding code in `exif-data.c` that iterates over IFD entries,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaying close attention to brace matching and indentation.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The function boundaries in `exif-data.c` around lines [0m[1;36m520[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m580[0m[39m, where the patch[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwas applied, to restore correct syntax.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Adjacent conditional or switch statements that may have been inadvertently [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maltered by the patch.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The signature of `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnumber and types of parameters[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto ensure the patch’s call matches the function prototype.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
